<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="91" pageId="0" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="91" pageId="0" pageNumber="90" type="mainText">
According to Folkrnanova (1940:47) 
<taxonomicName authority="Latzel, 1880" authorityName="Latzel" authorityYear="1880" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Polybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="91" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloryastygis">
Polybothrus 
<pageBreakToken pageId="1" pageNumber="91" start="start">gloryastygis</pageBreakToken>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriaslygis">Eupolybothrus gloriaslygis</taxonomicName>
) WAS named and pictured by Absolon (1916). Later (1940), Folkmanova made quite a good redescription of this peculiar eupolybotrid, based on the original material. In the same period, Hoffer (1935) described from Golograznica cave near Rishan (ex-Yugoslavia) another member of 
<taxonomicName pageId="1" pageNumber="91" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ethopolyinae">Ethopolyinae</taxonomicName>
, which he named 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Bothropolys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus">Bothropolys magnificus</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus">Eupolybothrus magnificus</taxonomicName>
). The latter is closely related to the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Absolonâ€™s" pageId="1" pageNumber="91">Absolon's</normalizedToken>
species which is why Matic &amp; Darabantu (1968), having studied a material collected in some Yugoslav caves, synonymised 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriastygis">Eupolybothrus gloriastygis</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus">Eupolybothrus magnificus</taxonomicName>
, incorrectly giving priority to 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus">Eupolybothrus magnificus</taxonomicName>
. According to International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, priority should be given to the older name 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriastygis">E. gloriastygis</taxonomicName>
(reported and described in 1916), while 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus">E. magnificus</taxonomicName>
becomes its junior synonym. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffer, 1935" authorityName="Hoffer," authorityYear="1935" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnificus" subGenus="Eupolybothrus">
Eupolybothrus (Eupolybothrus) magnificus (
<authority pageId="1" pageNumber="91">Hoffer, 1935</authority>
)
</taxonomicName>
is thus a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Absolon, 1916" authorityName="Absolon," authorityYear="1916" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriastygis" subGenus="Eupolybothrus">
Eupolybothrus (Eupolybothrus) gloriastygis (
<authority pageId="1" pageNumber="91">Absolon, 1916</authority>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="1" pageNumber="91">n. ressur.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="91" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="91" type="mainText">
Up to now, 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Eupolybothrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriastygis">Eupolybothrus gloriastygis</taxonomicName>
is known from a few caves in Herzegovina and Montenegro only.
</paragraph>
